  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This UoA evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Intended use is bounded to adult CPB circuits operating at 2–6 L/min flow and 1 500–3 500 RPM impeller speed; the model output is normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) for regulatory submission to FDA under 21 CFR 870.4360.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/hemolysis-prediction-cpb",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/nih-worst-case-cpb",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/cfd-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-pump-piv-measurements",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-bench"
  ],
